Name: Fallout 4 Essentials
Author: CrowsBane
Description: Fallout 4 Essentials with optional Sim Settlements 2 support.

State.Name: FallOpt - Lightweight ENB for Vanilla weather
State.Author: SpringHeelJon
State.Description: Featured in the Welcome to Paradise Wabbajack modlist by Phoenix, FallOpt is an optimized ENB for the vanilla weather system.

State.Name: xSE PluginPreloader F4
State.Author: Karandra
State.Description: This mod allows preload F4SE plugins before the game initializes.

State.Name: Buffout 4
State.Author: Ryan
State.Description: It's like buffout but for the engine

State.Name: Better Companions - No Conflicts
State.Author: Recluse
State.Description: Combines the effects of Companion Infinite Ammo, No Companion Power Armor Damage, Companions Can Sneak, and No Companion Fall Damage, for vanilla, DLC, and Mod Companions, WITHOUT making any edits to vanilla records and WITHOUT scripts. No overwrites, no conflicts. Now with Increased Companion Accuracy option.

State.Name: Binary Speech Checks
State.Author: Henke
State.Description: Makes the speech checks binary like in New Vegas. Removing the random element from them. Made in FO4Edit!

State.Name: BS Defence - This Settlement Does Not Need Your Help
State.Author: Rcoll
State.Description: Better Settlement Defence - Makes those hundreds of turrets actually do something when you're not around by taking away the random aspect of settlement attacks.

State.Name: Canary Save File Monitor
State.Author: kinggath
State.Description: Monitors your save file for data loss and warns you when you load the game, so you can avoid wasting time playing on a busted save and roll back immediately.

State.Name: Choochoo1's Workshop Framework displays
State.Author: Choochoo1
State.Description: This mod adds several displays for your items as well as a few random clutter items for your settlments. Allowing you show off your favorite weapon, store all that Nuka Cola you have been carrying around  or place your magazines on a more space efficient wall shelf.

State.Name: Clarity - A Visual Overhaul
State.Author: Bretton
State.Description: A zero performance loss, very subtle visual overhaul. Removes many annoying visuals in the game.

State.Name: Commonwealth Climate - A Vanilla Plus Weather Mod
State.Author: Qolore7
State.Description: Makes Fallout 4 a little more bleak/post-apocalyptic without completely changing the game's aesthetics

Archives.Name: Follower Stealth Distance Fix (No Free Hugs) - ESL-tagged-15823-7-0-1620077127.7z

State.Name: Companion Stealth Distance Fix (No Free Hugs) - Now with No Dogmeat in Crosshairs
State.Author: spacefiddle
State.Description: A simple change that prevents your companion from charging up your posterior at full speed whenever you enter stealth. Also slightly increases their follow distance. Now also prevents Dogmeat from entering player crosshairs every damn time you stop!

State.Name: Configurable Hotkeys
State.Author: Dank Rafft
State.Description: Configure several hotkeys via MCM that allow you to create standard saves, use items, wait anywhere, execute console commands or custom functions.

State.Name: Craftable Turret Stands
State.Author: Daedragon
State.Description: Lets you craft the wooden turret stands found in Covenant. A must-have for those who like to go heavy on the turrets!

State.Name: Creation Club - Better Military Backpack Distribution
State.Author: Hackfield
State.Description: A backpack won't magically appear in your inventory when installing the mod, instead, a blue Vault-Tec backpack is placed in Vault 111. Also, world distributed backpacks will now have random colors and modifications.

State.Name: Easy Lockpicking and Hacking
State.Author: Dank Rafft
State.Description: Since the original mod has some flaws (missing master, form and a wild edit) which could lead to an automatically deactivating mod or unnecessary mod conflicts I decided to recreate it. V2 also includes easy hacking.

State.Name: Extended Dialogue Interface
State.Author: reg2k and Neanka
State.Description: The Extended Dialogue Interface removes the hardcoded 4-option limit on dialogue and adds full engine support for any number of player dialogue options.

State.Name: FallUI - Inventory
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description: This is FallUI - Inventory. A optimized Fallout 4 inventory interface for PC.

Archives.Name: Fallout 4 Vanilla incl. All DLCs (All languages)-49656-1-13-1623855803.rar

State.Name: FallUI - Item Sorter Mod
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description: The official Item Sorter Mod for FallUI. Available for all languages.

State.Name: FallUI - Map
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description: Overhaul of the Fallout 4 map. Added list of locations and workshops including text search. Add favorite locations to fast travel with one click. Many Quality-Of-Life features like disabling the popup on empty map space click, better map zoom steps, travel and arrival time. Colored marker support. Including high-res map texture support.

State.Name: FallUI - Sleep and Wait
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description:
Overhaul of the sleeping and waiting menu for Fallout 4. 

Directly click on your desired wake-up time with target time buttons. See the daylight level at target time in the daytime graph and more. Interface available in all languages.

State.Name: FallUI - Workbench
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description: Better workbench interface optimized for PC. Bigger display size. Data columns. Comparision columns for mods. Item icon tag support. Icon menu for choosing your icon tag. Item subtitles. Autobuilding modules with zero cost. All languages included.

State.Name: FAR - Faraway Area Reform
State.Author: SparrowPrince
State.Description: FAR optimises and improves over six thousand distant land textures, which means more perfomance and less stutter.

State.Name: Flicker Fixer
State.Author: Glass
State.Description: Fixes most of the exterior flickering aka z fighting in the game, particularly in the Boston and Cambridge areas.

Archives.Name: Fortune Finder 4 Fix - Basic Bottlecap Mine-43740-1-1-1583316002.7z

State.Name: Fortune Finder 4 Fix
State.Author: Whisper
State.Description:
An intense firefight, several opponents have exploded into caps. Money! Yay! Now that you're done, night's coming on and you've got to find the piles of caps spread all over...in the coming darkness...



...yeah screw that. Put those caps in my pocket, since you're that immersive and all. Same for them there Bottlecap Mines.

State.Name: Gear Grinder
State.Author: IDontEvenKnow
State.Description: Think stripping things down for parts is as tedious as I do? Here's a machine to automate the process.

State.Name: Graf's Security Fences
State.Author: GrafPanzer
State.Description: Adds buildable, snappable barbed-wire topped security fences to the Workshop Fences menu.  Variants have sheet metal screening or concrete block reinforcement.  Script-added menu plays nicely with other mods.  Now with pre-war variants and auto-closing gates.  Versión en español disponible.

State.Name: HUDFramework
State.Author: registrator2000

State.Name: IDEK's Logistics Station 2
State.Author: IDontEvenKnow
State.Description:
Now with support for SimSettlements 1 and 2, or no SS at all!

Adds a system to automatically manage supply lines, improve the efficiency of inter-settlement resource sharing, and adds a handful of minor convenience features.

State.Name: Immersive HUD - iHUD
State.Author: Gopher
State.Description: HUD when you need. Hide when you don't.

State.Name: Laser weapons 1st person reposition
State.Author: akir4 and Wardaddy
State.Description: Makes the institute and standard laser weapons smaller in the 1st person.

State.Name: MCM Settings Manager
State.Author: m8r98a4f2
State.Description: Save, load, transfer, import and export all your MCM settings at once. Transfer settings between savegames, backup your favorite settings, or send your settings to another user!

State.Author: payl0ad
State.Description: New higher detail LOD Object Textures upscaled by Neural Networks

State.Name: No Aggro Impact Landing (Power Armor)

State.Name: No Negative Affinity and No Affinity Cooldown
State.Author: ricky horror
State.Description: Removes negative affinity effects from gameplay, as well as a few other options available. And has the option to remove affinity cooldown timers, as well as a few other options for that as well.

Are you sick of scrapping your settlements to the ground so you can build on them? Me too.



One click of a button in a holotape - gone in sixty seconds! (Depending upon the power of your gaming rig.)

State.Name: Rusty Face Fix
State.Author: Seb263
State.Description: This mod fixes this annoying bug that makes the player's and NPCs faces turn brown when reloading a savegame. It is completely transparent, autonomous, has no impact on performance and is compatible with any mods.

State.Name: Un-Randomized Workshop Turrets
State.Author: Yukichigai
State.Description: Removes the random distribution on workshop (and all other) turrets so that you always get the same "Mk. I"/"Mk. VII"/etc. turret on deploy, instead of a randomized one.

State.Name: Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch
State.Author: Unofficial Patch Project Team
State.Description: A comprehensive bugfixing mod for Fallout 4. The goal of the Unofficial Fallout 4 Patch (aka UFO4P) is to eventually fix every bug with Fallout 4 not officially resolved by the developers to the limits of the Creation Kit and community-developed tools, in one easy-to-install package.

State.Name: Vault 88 Essentials
State.Author: SethNorris
State.Description: Combination, improvement and bug fixing for several popular Vault 88 Kit mods plus a small set of additions. The bare essentials for a proper Vault building experience.

State.Name: Vault 88 Template - Optimised
State.Author: RyReZar
State.Description: This mod adds Room Bounds and Portals to a custom template of Vault 88 which gives greater optimisation and allows a bigger vault to be built, essentially increasing the build limit.

State.Name: Vault-Tec Workshop Overhaul Redux (VTWOR)
State.Author: litbeep
State.Description: A non-intrusive mod that aims to fix inconsistencies within the Vault-Tec Workshop DLC. This version addresses lighting and texture issues, adds light snapping to walls and ceilings, adds sign snapping to doors, enables crate stacking, and makes some minor quality-of-life changes.

State.Name: Visible Idle Markers
State.Author: Whisper
State.Description: So you built something in your settlement - only to find that your settlers "phase in" to it, because there's an idle marker there. No more - now you can see the base game idle markers while in workshop mode.

State.Description: Some extra kitbashed floors and ceilings, and extra snap-points upon many vanilla wood/metal build-items.

State.Name: Workshop Framework
State.Author: kinggath

Framework to open up the settlement system to editing by the community.



For Players: New controls and faster, more stable workshop scripts.



For Modders: Add new resource types, override settings, and generally change the way settlements work dynamically.

State.Name: Workshop Plus
State.Author: kinggath
State.Description:
Transforms Workshop mode into a God simulator - giving you all of the tools you need to create amazing settlements. 



Flight, Undo Buttons, Layers, Cloning Tools, Free Build Mode, and more!

State.Description: A highly configurable HUD. Every widget can be positioned and configured. Configure your design in the in-game layout manager in MCM. Layouts can be shared and imported too.

Also provides a hotkey to instantly enter Workshop mode and fixes workshop icon load lag.
